Executive Profile
Terence H. Matthews  Co-Founder and Chairman, Mitel Networks CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 15 Board Members in 15 different organizations across 20 different industries.See Board Relationships74$236,200
Background

		Dr. Terence H. Matthews, also known as Terry, serves as a Vice President of Business Development of  Mosaic Technologies Corporation. Dr. Matthews serves as Advisor of Cambrai Solutions Inc. He serves as the Chairman of CounterPath Corporation. He is the Founder of Wesley Clover Corporation. He co-founded Mitel Networks Corporation in 1972 and served as its Owner and Chief Executive Officer. He served as Chief Executive Officer of March Networks Corporation from June ... 2000 to 2004. He has either founded or funded over 80 companies since 1972. In February 2001, Dr. Matthews purchased British Telecom’s worldwide Communications Systems division and the Mitel name. Prior to March Networks, he served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Alcatel-Lucent Canada Inc. from June 1986 to May 2000, a company he founded in 1986. Providing leadership and vision for 14 years, Dr. Matthews helped Newbridge become a leader in the worldwide data networking industry. He was the Founder and Principal Investor in Celtic House Venture Partners Inc. He was employed at Microsystems International Limited. He was Co-Founder of Raseen Technologies L.L.C. He is a majority owner and the Chairman of The Brookstreet Resort. He serves as Chairman of the Board of Wesley Clover Corporation, Martello Technologies, Inc., Cambrai Solutions Inc. and The Celtic Manor Resort in Wales. He has been Chairman of March Networks Corporation since June 2000. He has been the Chairman and Director at Mitel Networks Corporation since February 16, 2001. He serves as the Non-Executive Chairman of Newport Networks Group Plc. He serves as Chairman of ProntoForms Corporation, Teldio Corporation, Benbria Corporation and Magor Corporation. He serves as Chairman for a number of high technology companies including Counterpath Corporation, Crosskeys Systems Corporations and NewHeights Software. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Solace Systems, Inc. until September 2016. He served as the Chairman of Bridgewater Systems Corporation, Tundra Semiconductor Corporation and Convedia Corporation. He has been a Director at TrueContext Mobile Solutions Corporation August 11, 2009. He serves as a Member of Governing Council at Canadian Advanced Technology Alliance. He serves as a Director at Newport Networks Group Plc, Teldio Corporation and Magor Communications Corporation. Dr. Matthews serves as a Director of Yupiq Corporation Limited. He has been a Director of Magor Corporation since June 2007 and ProntoForms Corporation since August 11, 2009. He has been a Director of CounterPath Corporation since August 2, 2007. He has been a Director of March Networks Corporation since April 20, 1998. He served as a Director of Bridgewater Systems since April 1997 and Division Optoelectronic and Microelectronic Design and Manufacturing. He served as a Director at Orchestream Canada Corporation, Carlaw Capital II Corp., Sanmina-SCI Corporation, Ubiquity Software Corporation Limited, FastLane Technologies, Inc. and Redback Networks Systems Canada, Inc. He served as a Member of Advisory Board of OMERS Ventures. Dr. Matthews served as a Director at Dragonwave Inc. from March 30, 2000 to June 12, 2012. He served as a Director of ImagicTV Inc. since January 1998 and Natural Convergence, Inc. since August 2004. In 1994, he was appointed an Officer of the Order of the British Empire and in the Queen’s Birthday Honours 2001, he was awarded a Knighthood. In 2011, he was appointed Patron of the European Cancer Stem Cell Research Institute. He is a Fellow of the Institute of Electrical Engineers and of the Royal Academy of Engineering. He holds a Kt.,OBE, P.Eng., and F.I.E.E. F R Eng. He holds an Honors degree in Electronics from the University of Wales and Swansea. Dr Matthews has been awarded honorary doctorates the University of Wales, Glamorgan and Swansea and Carleton University in Ottawa.Read Full Background




